'''Christmas in the Park''' is the title given to annual free music concerts held in cities across [[New Zealand]] during the Christmas season. The two largest Christmas in the Park events, held in [[Auckland]] and [[Christchurch]] since 1994, are sponsored by [[Coca-Cola]]. They draw up to 250,000<ref name=Hunkin>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/christmas-in-the-park/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501006&objectid=10547876|title=Star far from home for park gig - Christmas in the Park - NZ Herald News|publisher=www.nzherald.co.nz|accessdate=2009-02-01|date=2008-12-13|last=Hunkin|first=Joanna}}</ref> and 100,000<ref name=the_hub/> spectators, respectively. Coca-Cola refers to its Auckland Christmas in the Park production as the largest free annual event in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christmasinthepark.co.nz/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2&Itemid=2 |title=Coca-Cola Christmas in the Park - Auckland |accessdate=2009-01-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081221222523/http://www.christmasinthepark.co.nz/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2&Itemid=2 |archivedate=December 21, 2008 }}</ref> A combined total of six million New Zealanders have attended the Auckland and Christchurch events since their founding.<ref name=eventfinder2007>{{cite web|url=http://www.eventfinder.co.nz/2007/dec/auckland/christmas-in-the-park|title=Coca Cola Christmas in the Park - Auckland Central - Eventfinder|publisher=www.eventfinder.co.nz|accessdate=2009-02-01}}</ref> Activities include music, [[fireworks]] displays, and the lighting of [[Christmas tree]]s. Each concert draws an estimated $100,000 for charity annually.<ref name=the_hub>{{cite web|url=http://the-hub.tv/content/view/889/92/|title=The Hub - Coca-Cola Christmas in the Park|publisher=the-hub.tv|accessdate=2009-02-01}}</ref>
