{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}

The '''parcel mule scam''', also known as the '''reshipping scam''', involves scammers and unsuspecting victims handling goods<ref name="reg">{{cite journal|last=Leyden|first=John|journal=The Register|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2008/10/28/parcel_mule_scam/ | title = Parcel mules scam exposed: Cybercrook, keen phisherman seeks reliable partners on dating sites | date = 28 October 2008}}</ref> to other countries. In some ways it is similar to the [[money mule]] scam. Scammers use fake advertising<ref name="compact">{{cite web|url=http://www.computeractive.co.uk/computeractive/news/2229142/fraudsters-target-vulnerable|title=Criminals dupe vulnerable into handling stolen goods: Fraudsters targeting women on dating websites in particular |last=Greek|first=Dinah| accessdate = 15 February 2015 | publisher = Computeract!ve | date = 27 October 2008 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081031210639/http://www.computeractive.co.uk/computeractive/news/2229142/fraudsters-target-vulnerable | archive-date = 31 October 2008}}</ref> to hire mules. Items are bought with [[Carding (fraud)|stolen cards]],<ref name="compact" /> and since the goods are typically re-sold once shipped, this scam can be viewed as an indirect form of [[money laundering]].

== Example ==

One famous scam was organized under the "Air Parcel Express" corporate name.<ref name="rsa">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsa.com/blog/blog_entry.aspx?id=1541|title=Deep Inside a Reshipping Scam: Mules Victimized by "Air Parcel Express"| accessdate = 16 February 2015 | author = RSA FraudAction Research Lab | date = 12 November 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100813120659/http://www.rsa.com/blog/blog_entry.aspx?id=1541 | archive-date = 13 August 2010}}</ref> Criminals purchased items in the United States<ref name="reg" /> and sent them via mules<ref name="reg" /> to [[Russia]] and [[Belarus]],<ref name="rsa" /> where they were then sold. Items included iPods, PlayStations, smartphones, and laptops.<ref name="rsa" />

